[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The concept is simple, but the implications to the AI creative video space are pretty significant. Welcome back to the channel where we discuss the creative uses of AI. Literick\'s new LTX2 audiotov video model purports to take audio and then with a prompt or an image'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'or a combination of both, turn it into a video that is based on and will synchronize with the audio. And if you are interested in making music videos where the musicians are playing with the music, you\'ve got to check this out because even though this is not perfect'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'yet, this is a technology that you are going to want to watch. Not all platforms have adopted this model yet, but we do have it over at Open Art. Now, with my very first test, I got to tell you, I think I got lucky. I simply put a text prompt. A man is riding a subway. And this is the audio I gave it.'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Amen. And speaking of online things, my sister told me today because you Well, actually, you know, you get your glasses. &gt;&gt; And here\'s what I got. &gt;&gt; And then and speaking of online things, my sister told me today because you Well, actually, you know, you get your'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'glasses from a professional, do you not? The glasses you\'re wearing right now are professionally. Now, I didn\'t have any other background noises going on in that audio because I really wasn\'t clear of what the model was capable of. It was only through the subsequent testing that'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I realized how to unlock some of its power. But even in this case, we got the lip sync. And one of the things to notice is that his facial expressions and movement are reacting to the emotional arc of whatever he\'s saying. Now, there wasn\'t a huge emotional arc'

[01:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'there, but when he stressed certain things, his facial expressions matched what he was stressing. Also, we have full activity going on in the background, even though I didn\'t have any sound associated with it. So to make my test more interesting, I decided to create little sound scenarios where'

[01:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'there is background audio that would go along with whatever was going on in the video. Started with something very simple, just a man being in his car. So I recorded this audio. Uh yeah. Hey, [clears throat] it\'s uh pretty much'

[01:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'impossible for me to tell you when I\'m going to be there because traffic. Hey, what what do you want me to tell you? I can\'t tell you when I\'m going to get back. Stop pissing me off and just let me get there. I intentionally put an emotional arc where he starts with a little bit of frustration and then'

[01:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually gets angry because I wanted to see what the model would do. This is the starting image I gave it and the prompt is a man is riding through the city in his car talking on a speaker phone trying to explain in an angry tone that he cannot confirm when he is going to'

[02:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'arrive at his destination. Now, you\'ll notice in this case I did not put any text in quotes or anything like that. I just simply gave it the audio file and that prompt and this picture. And here\'s what we got. &gt;&gt; Ah, yeah. Hey, it\'s [clears throat] uh pretty much impossible for me to tell'

[02:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you when I\'m going to be there because traffic Hey, what what do you want me to tell you? I can\'t tell you when I\'m going to get back. Stop pissing me off and just let me get there. Okay, I\'ll call you back. So, I like how the car started to pull off after he was done'

[02:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'talking. The lip sync did get a little soft there at the end, but again, you can see that the city was alive and he was accurately expressing the emotion that was being spoken. Here\'s another example. Same exact audio, different picture. Ah, yeah. Hey,'

[02:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[clears throat and cough] it\'s uh pretty much impossible for me to tell you when I\'m going to be there because traffic. Hey, what what do you want me to tell you? I can\'t tell you when I\'m going to get back. Stop pissing me off and just let me get there. Okay, I\'ll call you'

[02:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'back. So, even though the model can infer a good bit from just what\'s going on in the image, the more you give it in terms of expression and emotional arc and specific things that you want it to say or do, the better the model does with it. So, I wanted to see what this'

[03:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'audio and this prompt would do if I wasn\'t using an image to start it with. just used the text to video capabilities to see what it came up with. So, our prompt was just a close-up Dutch angle front view. A mysterious crime fighting man is racing a black and purple Ferrari'

[03:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'down a busy city street at dusk with an angry look on his face. So, this is his mysterious crime fighting outfit. And he is in a We can only assume that this is a blue and purple Ferrari. And I will also note that I did not type out the'

[03:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'script of what I wanted him to say. And yet, we got this. Ah, yeah. Hey, it\'s [clears throat] uh pretty much impossible for me to tell you when I\'m going to be there because traffic. Hey, what what do you want me to tell you? I can\'t tell you when I\'m going to get'

[03:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'back. Stop pissing me off and just let me get there. Okay, I\'ll call you back. You can see him get annoyed and the lip sync is perfect and the sound in the background goes along with it just great, even without telling the model exactly what to say. However, that is'

[03:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'not always the case. Again, another one of my early tests was simply a text prompt that grandmother is baking cookies and talking to the camera as it dollies around her as she mixes the ingredients. And I had this audio file to go with it.'

[04:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; What do I like to talk about? Well, Sunno has a few features that have me a bit excited. &gt;&gt; So, I figured it would do a lip sync as she talked, but instead we got this. &gt;&gt; What do I like to talk about? Well,'

[04:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Sunno has a few features. Basically, we didn\'t get anything in terms of lip-s sync. So, that\'s when I started using text prompts, and I get much more consistent results that way. Here\'s an example of what I mean. I have this'

[04:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'image here of this woman who is clearly upset and crying, talking on the phone. I acted out a little monologue and did some voice changing and put some real emotion into it. &gt;&gt; I am clear that this is not important to you.'

[04:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Then the prompt is, a woman on the phone is very upset and crying, saying, and now I say exactly what she says. That gives us this. &gt;&gt; I am clear that this is not important to you,'

[05:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'but it is extremely important to me and my family. So, you get your ass here. Now, &gt;&gt; a lot going on there, but notably the little breathe in that she does, the little gasp at the beginning. It'

[05:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'captures that visually. &gt;&gt; I am &gt;&gt; right there. Now, to amp it up a little bit, this time I added some sentimental music in the background and actually said that she\'s very upset and that she has tears streaming down her face. &gt;&gt; I am clear that this is not important'

[05:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[music] to you, but it is extremely important to me [music] and my family. So, you get your ass here now.'

[05:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; And I love the fact that she even leans in to maybe hang up the phone. Of course, the picture gets all messed up here, but I am pretty freaking impressed with that. In this example, I had a monster and a waitress, and the prompt is, "A monster and a waitress are having'

[05:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'an argument." The monster, who should be very obvious visually, says, "Lady, I asked for a ham and cheese." And the waitress says, "No, you didn\'t. You asked for a cheese and ham." And the dialogue continues. Now, in this particular example, that\'s not exactly'

[06:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'what the audio said. I did not recreate it word for word. I just gave it the gist. Here\'s the actual audio. Lady, I asked for ham and cheese. No, you didn\'t. You asked for cheese and ham. I said ham and cheese. I clearly said it.'

[06:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I even asked you to repeat it. No, you didn\'t. We have witnesses. Obviously, I didn\'t do any AI voice changes. I just did drastically different reads between the two characters so that the model would hopefully know who\'s the monster'

[06:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and who\'s the woman. We get this. Now, watch both of their mouths here at the beginning. &gt;&gt; Lady, I asked for ham and cheese. No, you didn\'t. You asked for cheese and ham. I said ham and cheese. I clearly said it. I even asked you to repeat it. No, you didn\'t. if we have witnesses.'

[06:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, most of the time the monster was saying everything for both parts and she only joined in at the end. Here\'s another example where I\'ve got two different people talking and I\'ve got a sound effect going in the background. So, I just created this dialogue of'

[06:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'these two construction workers and put in a sound of an explosion. Sounds like this. &gt;&gt; Hey, uh you\'re not thinking about blowing up that building back there, are you? &gt;&gt; What? That building back there? &gt;&gt; Yeah, that one. &gt;&gt; So, that\'s all the audio there is. And'

[07:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then this picture of these two guys. We got black pants. We got brown pants. We got a building back there. However, I was not specific with every line of dialogue. I say, "The man in the black pants ask the man in the brown pants if he\'s going to blow up the building." I'

[07:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'don\'t have him say, "Hey, you aren\'t thinking about blowing up that building back there." And in this line, I say, "The man in the brown pants turns back to look at the building." And the man in the beard, who is actually the same guy as the man with the brown pants, I just wanted to state it differently, says,'

[07:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '"This building back there." And then the man in the black pants says, "Yeah, that one." and the man in the beard and the brown pants pushes down the plunger on the detonator and the building explodes in the background. However, with that prompt, we get this. &gt;&gt; Hey, uh, you\'re not thinking about'

[07:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'blowing up that building back there, are you? &gt;&gt; What? That building back there? &gt;&gt; Yeah, that one. &gt;&gt; So, there\'s a few problems with that. Mainly, we got the guy with the beard doing most of the talking after the guy'

[08:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with the black pants starts. Let\'s watch again at the very beginning and watch what happens with the lips. &gt;&gt; Hey, uh, you\'re not thinking about blue. So, hey, uh, it started with the guy in the black pant, and then you\'re not thinking about continuing with there. And then the building didn\'t really blow'

[08:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'up, but we did have some sort of an explosion that did synchronize with the sound. So, instead of asking the model to infer who was saying what just based on the dialogue, I gave it help and told it exactly what each person was saying. And now, at least the speaking is'

[08:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'correct. &gt;&gt; Hey, uh, you\'re not thinking about blowing up that building back there, are you? &gt;&gt; What? That building back there? &gt;&gt; Yeah, that one. The main issue with that generation is'

[08:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that the explosion is supposed to happen after he does the plunger. So maybe I should have put a sound effect of a plunger being pushed. Now just before we move on to the music examples, which are very, very cool and exciting, at least in terms of the implication of where'

[08:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this is going, let\'s do one more example where I produced an audio piece that has lots of sound effects going on, and then I prompted a starting image that had all of those audio elements in it potentially. So, I created this image of a man standing in a workshop and he\'s'

[09:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'got a guy sawing, he\'s got a guy hammering, and then there\'s an electric saw over here. Here\'s the audio. You know, sometimes out at the construction site, things get pretty noisy, but at least I got my buddies here to keep me honest and are quiet when I try to talk.'

[09:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Except for Steve and his stupid saw, Steve. So, obviously, I was hoping for all sorts of coordinated audio and video with the sound effects and people sawing and people hammering. Here\'s what we got the first time around. You know,'

[09:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sometimes out at the construction site, things get pretty noisy, but at least I got my buddies here to keep me honest and are quiet when I try to talk. Except for Steve and his stupid saw, Steve. So, I wanted a little more frustration'

[09:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with him and I wanted the saw to be noticeably turned on at that particular time. And the guy with a hammer was just kind of holding the hammer. So, I got more specific with the prompt and said, "We actually see a man with a hammer hammering a piece of wood and a man with'

[09:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a saw sawing on a 2x4 and still another guy with an electric saw that he starts while the man is talking." I even try to break it up into sections where I say, "At least I got my buddies here to keep me honest." And they\'re quiet when I try to talk because that\'s really the cue'

[10:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for Steve to turn on his electric drill. So, I say the man with the table saw turns it on and starts cutting wood and then the man in the front continues talking except for Steve and his stupid saw. Steve. Now, remember, all the timing of this is 100% based on the'

[10:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'audio, so there\'s no leeway of when things are going to happen. I just want to make sure that they do. And here\'s what we got with that revised prompt. You know, sometimes out at the construction site, things get pretty noisy, but at least I got my buddies'

[10:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here to keep me honest and they\'re quiet when I try to talk. Except for Steve and his stupid saw, Steve. So, not that much difference, but we did get much more frustration from him this'

[10:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'time. So, I thought, well, how about if I don\'t confine it to an image and just let the text to video model do its thing and see what we get. So, same exact prompt, except that I don\'t give it any visual help. You know, sometimes out at the construction site, things get pretty'

[10:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'noisy, but at least I got my buddies here to keep me honest and are quiet when I try to talk. Except for Steve and his stupid saw. Steve. So, the hammering and the sawing that we heard at the'

[11:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'beginning was not really coordinated. Although, when we mentioned Steve and his saw, we did see it go on here in the background. And here\'s one more try at this. You know, sometimes out at the construction site, things get pretty noisy. But at least I got my buddies here to keep me honest and they\'re quiet'

[11:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'when I try to talk. Except for Steve and his stupid saw. Steve, I love the emotional expression here. But we don\'t even see Steve in his electric saw. Now, let\'s get into the music part because this is really,'

[11:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'really cool. Now, I\'m a musician. I play the ukulele. I play the keyboards, things like that. And whenever I do any kind of AI video, the best I can do is hope that if I\'ve got a model like Cling 2.6 Motion Control, it\'ll track my fingers and that kind of thing. But I'

[11:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have to do a live performance for it to even come close to looking like I\'m actually playing what you\'re hearing. But this model kind of solves that. So I started with just this picture of me playing the ukulele on the beach. And then this audio. [music] Okay. Hey, the man is playing the'

[12:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ukulele as massive waves roll into shore. Here\'s the first result we got. [music] &gt;&gt; [music]'

[12:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Now, of course, it did not do all the lefth hand fingering work accurately, but the rhythm was right. It stopped when the music stopped. And the only other comment was like, "Hey, Bob, why'

[12:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so serious?" So, I changed the prompt to say, "He\'s smiling while playing the ukulele." And I tried to get a little bit more accuracy on the left hand by saying, "We see his fingers on his left hand play all the notes." But this is what we got. &gt;&gt; [music]'

[12:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; So, even though it\'s not doing the left hand fingering, this is the closest I\'ve'

[13:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'gotten to this kind of accuracy when it comes to musical instrument playing. But it didn\'t stop at ukulele. Here, the starting image is me just sitting at the piano. And then we\'ve got this little riff. I say the man is smiling at the camera'

[13:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'while playing a jazzy piano song as the man in the far background gets up and dances. Now, in this particular image, there wasn\'t a man. That prompt was from an earlier test and I\'d forgotten about that. So, let\'s see what it does. [music]'

[13:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, the hands are not in the right place'

[13:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'or playing the right notes, but they\'re in time with the music. And to the casual viewer who may not be a musician or watching the hands that closely, it\'s just going to work better psychologically for them if the musicians are moving in time and rhythm with the music. Now, this guy\'s dance'

[13:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'was a little melancholy, but they did bring him in even though he wasn\'t in the original image. The starting image is a picture of my friend Rob. We used a more upbeat piece of music here. &gt;&gt; [music]'

[14:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; still have the man dancing in the background via the prompt. And we get this. [music] The dancing guy gets me every time for'

[14:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so many reasons. But again, it\'s not accurate in terms of what the notes are playing, but the movement is there. Now, yes, it\'s blurry. The resolution is not that great, but we are early in this, my friends. Let\'s keep watching what it can'

[14:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'do. Here we\'ve got this starting image and this music. The prompt is, as the crowd goes crazy with enthusiasm, the girl is excitedly playing the drums as the lights pan'

[14:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'around the room and the camera dollies around the drummer. I don\'t know if lights can pan around the room. I don\'t know what I was thinking, but check this out. [music] &gt;&gt; [music]'

[15:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; So much more accurate with the drums. At least to a non- drummer like me, it looks more accurate. Looks like the symbols are hit when they\'re supposed to be hit and the snares are hit when they\'re supposed to be hit. Here\'s another example with a different'

[15:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'picture. Same exact audio. Same prompt. Does a better job of dollying this time. [music] &gt;&gt; [music]'

[15:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; I mean, come on. That is freaking impressive. Even I can do it. [music] So, even with its imperfections, if you'

[15:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'need B-roll of musicians, if you\'re doing an AI music video, you might want to look at this model just for even some of the shots. Here\'s just a couple of examples with illustrations instead of photographs. This is our starting image, and it is a man singing to a bashful'

[16:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'woman at a table in a fancy restaurant as people dine in the background. &gt;&gt; I know you\'re better than you know yourself. You think you\'re hiding from me on the'

[16:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'show. &gt;&gt; It chose to have him take a to off that cigarette. I didn\'t prompt that. Or how about this one? Woman is singing about working her overnight shift. She\'s pouring coffee and doesn\'t realize it\'s'

[16:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'overflowing all over the counter and on the man. Starting image, you\'ll hear the audio. Here\'s what it did. I pull [music] the cord, I pull the weight away from 2 to 7 a.m. while the neighbors [music] sleep from 2'

[16:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to 7 a.m. Broken promises. &gt;&gt; By the way, those last two audio clips were created on the Sun Auto platform, which I just did a video on the other day. Crazy stuff they\'re doing. You'

[16:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'might want to check that out. So, that\'s the LTX2 audiotovideo model in its current form. It does some cool stuff. It doesn\'t work perfectly all the time. It\'s definitely early in the development. But the concept of being able to take an audio clip and'

[17:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'extrapolate visuals from it. You can start with an audio and create a whole film from that eventually. If these are the types of technologies you like to stay in the know about, well, why not subscribe to this channel? Cuz we like to stay in the know about it, too. And'

[17:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'we talk about it all the time. &gt;&gt; If you subscribe now, I will not look for you. I will not pursue you. But if you do not, I will look for you. [music] I will find you. And I'

[17:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; [music]'
